urns 500\n   235â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   236â†’\n   237â†’## Iteration 12 â€” 2026-03-25T12:11:41Z â€” OK\n   238â†’- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n   239â†’\n   240â†’## Iteration 13 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   241â†’\n   242â†’**Item**: [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` â€” poll claim status\n   243â†’**Status**: Done\n   244â†’**Changes**:\n   245â†’- Added `GET /claim/:claimId` endpoint to `services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n   246â†’  - Requires JWT auth (wallet from context)\n   247â†’  - Looks up claim by UUID via `db.getReferralClaim(claimId)`\n   248â†’  - Returns 404 if claim not found OR if claim belongs to a different wallet (prevents enumeration)\n   249â†’  - Returns `{ claimId, amountLamports, status, txSignature? }` per FR-7 contract\n   250â†’  - `txSignature` only included when present (completed claims)\n   251â†’  - `amountLamports` returned as string (lamports-only accounting)\n   252â†’  - Error handling: catches and logs failures, returns 500\n   253â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   254â†’\n   255â†’## Iteration 13 â€” 2026-03-25T12:14:13Z â€” OK\n   256â†’- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n   257â†’\n   258â†’## Iteration 14 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   259â†’\n   260â†’**Item**: [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware\n   261â†’**Status**: Done\n   262â†’**Changes**:\n   263â†’- Added `import { createReferralRoutes } from \"./routes/referral.js\"` to `services/backend/src/index.ts`\n   264â†’- Added JWT auth middleware for `/referral/*` with `requireAllMethods: true` (ensures auth on GET + POST)\n   265â†’- Mounted routes with `app.route(\"/referral\", createReferralRoutes({ db, sql, config }))` after profile routes\n   266â†’- Passes all 3 deps required by `ReferralRoutesDeps`: `db` (from createDb), `sql` (raw postgres connection), `config` (from loadConfig)\n   267â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   268â†’\n   269â†’## Iteration 14 â€” 2026-03-25T12:17:10Z â€” OK\n   270â†’- **Log**: iteration-014.log\n   271â†’\n   272â†’## Iteration 15 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   273â†’\n   274â†’**Item**: [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: referral earnings recording after game settlement\n   275â†’**Status**: Done\n   276â†’**Changes**:\n   277â†’- Added `referralDefaultRateBps: number` to `SettleTxDeps` interface\n   278â†’- Added `recordReferralEarnings()` helper function in `settle-tx.ts`:\n   279â†’  - Takes roundId, gameType, feeBps, referralDefaultRateBps, and player list\n   280â†’  - Deduplicates players (handles Lord of RNGs multiple entries per player)\n   281â†’  - For each player: checks `getReferralLinkByReferee()` â†’ if referrer exists, gets rate via `getReferrerRate()` (KOL override)\n   282â†’  - Calculates `referrerEarned = feeLamports * referrerRateBps / 10000` and `refereeRebate = feeLamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%)\n   283â†’  - Inserts via `db.insertReferralEarning()` with all economic inputs preserved\n   284â†’  - Error handling: duplicate key (idempotent skip), other errors logged but don't fail settlement\n   285â†’- Called `recordReferralEarnings()` at end of `settleMatch()` (coinflip â€” 2 players) and `settleLordRound()` (lord â€” N players)\n   286â†’- Updated caller in `index.ts` to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: config.referralDefaultRateBps`\n   287â†’- Updated integration test to pass `referralDefaultRateBps: 1000` in SettleTxDeps\n   288â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   289â†’\n   290â†’## Iteration 15 â€” 2026-03-25T12:25:43Z â€” OK\n   291â†’- **Log**: iteration-015.log\n   292â†’\n   293â†’## Iteration 16 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   294â†’\n   295â†’**Item**: [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity\n   296â†’**Status**: Done\n   297â†’**Changes**:\n   298â†’- Added `withTransaction<T>(fn: (db: Db) => Promise<T>): Promise<T>` method to `Db` interface in `db.ts`\n   299â†’- Refactored `createDb()` to accept an optional `_txSql` parameter for transaction injection. When provided, the sql object is used directly (no new connection). `close()` is guarded to only close owned connections.\n   300â†’- `withTransaction` implementation uses `sql.begin()` to create a transaction scope and passes a transactional `Db` (via recursive `createDb(databaseUrl, txSql)`) to the callback\n   301â†’- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleMatch()`: wrapped all post-confirmation DB writes (updateRoundPhase, updateRoundEntries, insertOperatorEvent, insertTransaction, recordReferralEarnings) in `db.withTransaction()`\n   302â†’- In `settle-tx.ts` `settleLordRound()`: same wrapping for Lord of RNGs settlement writes\n   303â†’- All writes within the transaction use `txDb` instead of `db`, ensuring they share the same transaction connection\n   304â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   305â†’\n   306â†’## Iteration 16 â€” 2026-03-25T12:37:33Z â€” OK\n   307â†’- **Log**: iteration-016.log\n   308â†’\n   309â†’## Iteration 17 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   310â†’\n   311â†’**Item**: [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry\n   312â†’**Status**: Done\n   313â†’**Changes**:\n   314â†’- Created `services/backend/src/queue/handlers/referral-claim.ts` with `createClaimHandler()` factory\n   315â†’  - Accepts `ClaimHandlerDeps`: db, connection, serverKeypair\n   316â†’  - Returns an `EventHandler` function for the queue worker\n   317â†’  - Idempotent: skips if claim status is already `completed` or `failed`\n   318â†’  - Flow: load claim â†’ update to `processing` â†’ re-verify pending balance >= claim amount â†’ build SystemProgram.transfer tx â†’ send + confirm â†’ update to `completed` with tx_signature\n   319â†’  - On insufficient balance: updates to `failed` with descriptive error (no re-throw, terminal)\n   320â†’  - On transfer failure: updates to `failed` + re-throws so queue worker retries with exponential backoff\n   321â†’  - Uses web3.js v1 patterns consistent with settle-tx.ts (Transaction, sign, sendRawTransaction, confirmTransaction)\n   322â†’- Updated `services/backend/src/index.ts`:\n   323â†’  - Imported `registerHandler`, `EventTypes` from queue, and `createClaimHandler` from handler\n   324â†’  - Registered handler before event worker starts: `registerHandler(EventTypes.REFERRAL_CLAIM_REQUESTED, createClaimHandler({ db, connection, serverKeypair }))`\n   325â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Backend typecheck has 1 pre-existing error (HealthDeps in endpoints.test.ts) â€” no new errors introduced.\n   326â†’\n   327â†’## Iteration 17 â€” 2026-03-25T12:47:48Z â€” OK\n   328â†’- **Log**: iteration-017.log\n   329â†’\n   330â†’## Iteration 18 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   331â†’\n   332â†’**Item**: [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` â€” 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth\n   333â†’**Status**: Done\n   334â†’**Changes**:\n   335â†’- Created `apps/platform/src/lib/referral-api.ts` following `auth-api.ts` pattern\n   336â†’- Response type interfaces: `ReferralCodeResponse`, `ApplyReferralResponse`, `ReferralStatsResponse`, `ReferralEarningItem`, `ReferralEarningsResponse`, `ClaimResponse`\n   337â†’- Shared `parseResponse<T>()` utility with error extraction from `{ error: { message } }` shape\n   338â†’- `authHeaders(token)` helper for `Authorization: Bearer` + `Content-Type: application/json`\n   339â†’- 7 exported async functions: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings` (with optional page/limit query params), `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`\n   340â†’- All monetary values typed as `string` (lamports-only accounting)\n   341â†’- Fixed lint error: replaced `URLSearchParams` (not in ESLint globals) with manual query string construction\n   342â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18)\n   343â†’\n   344â†’## Iteration 18 â€” 2026-03-25T12:52:39Z â€” OK\n   345â†’- **Log**: iteration-018.log\n   346â†’\n   347â†’## Iteration 19 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   348â†’\n   349â†’**Item**: [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` â€” capture code to localStorage, redirect to `/`\n   350â†’**Status**: Done\n   351â†’**Changes**:\n   352â†’- Added `Navigate` and `useParams` imports from `react-router-dom` in `App.tsx`\n   353â†’- Created `ReferralCapture` component:\n   354â†’  - Reads `:code` from URL params via `useParams()`\n   355â†’  - Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` as JSON in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   356â†’  - Gracefully handles localStorage unavailability (private browsing, storage full)\n   357â†’  - Returns `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />` for immediate redirect\n   358â†’- Added `<Route path=\"/r/:code\" element={<ReferralCapture />} />` before the catch-all `*` route\n   359â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18). Platform typecheck passed. Pre-existing backend typecheck error (HealthDeps) â€” not introduced by this change.\n   360â†’\n   361â†’## Iteration 19 â€” 2026-03-25T12:58:52Z â€” OK\n   362â†’- **Log**: iteration-019.log\n   363â†’\n   364â†’## Iteration 20 â€” 2026-03-25 â€” OK\n   365â†’\n   366â†’**Item**: [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook â€” auto-apply stored referral code on authentication\n   367â†’**Status**: Done\n   368â†’**Changes**:\n   369â†’- Created `apps/platform/src/features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts`:\n   370â†’  - Watches `isAuthenticated`, `accessToken`, `address` from session/wallet hooks\n   371â†’  - Reads `referral_code` from localStorage (set by `/r/:code` ReferralCapture)\n   372â†’  - Calls `applyReferralCode(token, code)` on authentication\n   373â†’  - Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (ALREADY_LINKED, SELF_REFERRAL, NOT_FOUND, INVALID)\n   374â†’  - Keeps localStorage on transient failure (network error, 500) for retry on next auth\n   375â†’  - Uses `appliedRef` to prevent duplicate calls within same auth session\n   376â†’  - Handles corrupt/missing localStorage data gracefully\n   377â†’- Created `apps/platform/src/features/referral/index.ts` barrel export\n   378â†’- Updated `App.tsx`: imported `useReferralApply`, called in `AppContent` (inside auth provider tree)\n   379â†’**Verification**: `pnpm lint` passed (18/18, 0 errors). Platform typecheck passed. Pre-existing backend typecheck error (HealthDeps) â€” not introduced by this change.\n   380â†’\n   381â†’## Iteration 20 â€” 2026-03-25T13:06:04Z â€” OK\n   382â†’- **Log**: iteration-020.log\n   383â†’\n   384â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4718ef4b-5b78-4595-bd86-4abb58e68966","uuid":"023588ff-be9d-4c58-ade2-387ec5b539d0","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:06:25.927Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/history.md","content":"# Implementation History â€” 300-referral-system\n\nIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\nattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\nof every iteration to understand prior context.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 â€” 2026-03-24T21:27:27Z â€” OK\n\n**Item**: [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`\n**Status**: Done\n**Changes**:\n- Created `services/backend/migrations/011_referral.sql` with all 5 referral tables:\n  - `referral_codes` â€” one code per wallet (UNIQUE on wallet + code)\n  - `referral_links` â€” immutable referrer binding (UNIQUE on referee_wallet)\n  - `referral_earn