{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016LLQETxATWuLm4Pigt5jrq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1â†’# Specification: [300] Referral System\n     2â†’\n     3â†’## Meta\n     4â†’\n     5â†’| Field | Value |\n     6â†’|-------|-------|\n     7â†’| Status | Ready |\n     8â†’| Priority | P1 |\n     9â†’| Track | Extended |\n    10â†’| NR_OF_TRIES | 20 |\n    11â†’\n    12â†’---\n    13â†’\n    14â†’## Overview\n    15â†’\n    16â†’A Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can set a custom referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 â€” no program changes required.\n    17â†’\n    18â†’## User Stories\n    19â†’\n    20â†’- As a player, I want to set a custom referral code so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n    21â†’- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n    22â†’- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n    23â†’- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n    24â†’- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n    25â†’\n    26â†’---\n    27â†’\n    28â†’## Capability Alignment\n    29â†’\n    30â†’- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" â†’ \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n    31â†’- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n    32â†’- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n    33â†’\n    34â†’## Required Context Files\n    35â†’\n    36â†’- `docs/DECISIONS.md` â€” fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n    37â†’- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` â€” frontend entrypoint\n    38â†’- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` â€” on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n    39â†’- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n    40â†’\n    41â†’## Contract Files\n    42â†’\n    43â†’- No existing mocks â€” this is a new system\n    44â†’- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n    45â†’\n    46â†’---\n    47â†’\n    48â†’## System Invariants (v1)\n    49â†’\n    50â†’These invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n    51â†’\n    52â†’1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n    53â†’2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n    54â†’3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n    55â†’4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n    56â†’5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n    57â†’6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n    58â†’7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n    59â†’\n    60â†’---\n    61â†’\n    62â†’## Functional Requirements\n    63â†’\n    64â†’### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n    65â†’\n    66â†’Any player with a connected wallet can set a referral code. No eligibility gate â€” open from day one.\n    67â†’\n    68â†’**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n    69â†’\n    70â†’**Code format:**\n    71â†’- Player-chosen custom code: 3-16 characters, `[a-z0-9-]`, must be unique\n    72â†’- No auto-generation â€” the player always picks their own code\n    73â†’- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n    74â†’\n    75â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    76â†’- [ ] Authenticated player can set a referral code via API <!-- gap: routes/referral.ts does not exist -->\n    77â†’- [ ] Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique <!-- gap: no validation logic implemented -->\n    78â†’- [x] Each player has exactly one active code (setting a new one replaces the old one) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql UNIQUE(wallet) + db.ts:660 upsertReferralCode ON CONFLICT replaces -->\n    79â†’- [x] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates table + db.ts:637 insertReferralCode -->\n    80â†’\n    81â†’### FR-2: Referral Linking\n    82â†’\n    83â†’When a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n    84â†’\n    85â†’**Rules:**\n    86â†’- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n    87â†’- First code applied wins â€” cannot change referrer\n    88â†’- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n    89â†’\n    90â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    91â†’- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates <!-- gap: no /r/:code route in App.tsx -->\n    92â†’- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n    93â†’- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) <!-- gap: no POST /referral/apply endpoint or profile UI -->\n    94â†’- [x] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 referee_wallet UNIQUE + db.ts:694 insertReferralLink throws on duplicate -->\n    95â†’- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected <!-- gap: no API-level validation implemented -->\n    96â†’- [x] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:17-22 + db.ts:694-701 insertReferralLink -->\n    97â†’\n    98â†’### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n    99â†’\n   100â†’Referred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable â€” every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n   101â†’\n   102â†’**Economics:**\n   103â†’- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n   104â†’- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n   105â†’- Fee is charged in full on-chain â€” rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n   106â†’- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n   107â†’\n   108â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   109â†’- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n   110â†’- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n   111â†’- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n   112â†’- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   113â†’- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n   114â†’\n   115â†’### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n   116â†’\n   117â†’When a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n   118â†’\n   119â†’**Economics:**\n   120â†’- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4718ef4b-5b78-4595-bd86-4abb58e68966","uuid":"6f123c3e-7420-4c8e-a2ba-84031a850856","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:06:31.163Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"# Specification: [300] Referral System\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Priority | P1 |\n| Track | Extended |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 20 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nA Hyperliquid-style referral system where any player can set a custom referral code, share it, and earn a perpetual share of the platform fee from every game their referred players complete. Referred players receive a benefit for joining via a referral link (see FR-3 for options). The system is entirely off-chain for v1 â€” no program changes required.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to set a custom referral code so that I can invite friends and earn passive rewards from their gameplay\n- As a new player, I want to use a referral code so that I receive a signup benefit (fee rebate or bonus reward)\n- As a referrer, I want to see how many players I've referred and how much I've earned so that I can track my referral performance\n- As a referrer, I want to claim my accumulated earnings so that I receive SOL in my wallet\n- As an operator, I want to set custom referral rates for KOL wallets so that partnership agreements are honored\n\n---\n\n## Capability Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented in Current Baseline\" â†’ \"Referral and creator monetization systems\"\n- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n- **Planning bucket**: Extended\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `docs/DECISIONS.md` â€” fee structure (500 bps flat fee, single treasury via PlatformConfig)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/` â€” frontend entrypoint\n- `sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/` â€” on-chain fee constants (for reference, not modified)\n- Backend settlement logic (settlement worker, DB schema)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n- No existing mocks â€” this is a new system\n- API contract defined in FR-7 below\n\n---\n\n## System Invariants (v1)\n\nThese invariants are non-negotiable for correctness and abuse resistance:\n\n1. **Single referrer binding:** each referee wallet can be linked to only one referrer wallet for life (unless operator manually unlinks via admin tooling outside v1 scope).\n2. **No self-referral:** `referrer_wallet !== referee_wallet` enforced at API + DB layers.\n3. **Lamports-only accounting:** all stored/transported monetary values use integer lamports (`BIGINT` in DB, string in JSON APIs).\n4. **Atomic settlement + earning write:** referral earning insert must be in the same DB transaction as game settlement write.\n5. **Idempotent async handlers:** referral queue handlers must use domain keys (`claim_id`, `round_id + referee_wallet`, etc.), never `event_queue.id`, for de-duplication.\n6. **Exactly-once effect in practice:** queue may deliver at-least-once; side-effects must remain safe under replays.\n7. **No on-chain protocol changes:** v1 referral economics remain off-chain and treasury-operated.\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Referral Code Generation\n\nAny player with a connected wallet can set a referral code. No eligibility gate â€” open from day one.\n\n**Rationale:** The sybil incentive is negligible (max benefit from self-referral is 50 bps of wagered amount = referrer fee share, and self-referral is blocked on-chain). An eligibility gate hurts organic growth more than it prevents abuse.\n\n**Code format:**\n- Player-chosen custom code: 3-16 characters, `[a-z0-9-]`, must be unique\n- No auto-generation â€” the player always picks their own code\n- URL format: `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Authenticated player can set a referral code via API <!-- gap: routes/referral.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Code is always player-chosen, 3-16 chars, validated against `[a-z0-9-]`, unique <!-- gap: no validation logic implemented -->\n- [x] Each player has exactly one active code (setting a new one replaces the old one) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql UNIQUE(wallet) + db.ts:660 upsertReferralCode ON CONFLICT replaces -->\n- [x] Code is persisted in `referral_codes` table <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates table + db.ts:637 insertReferralCode -->\n\n### FR-2: Referral Linking\n\nWhen a player signs up or connects their wallet via a referral link (`taunt.bet/r/CODE`), they are permanently linked to the referrer. Alternatively, a player can manually enter a referral code in their settings.\n\n**Rules:**\n- One referrer per player, immutable once set\n- First code applied wins â€” cannot change referrer\n- Self-referral blocked (same wallet cannot be both referrer and referee)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Visiting `taunt.bet/r/{CODE}` stores the code (localStorage) until the player authenticates <!-- gap: no /r/:code route in App.tsx -->\n- [ ] On authentication, if the player has no referrer and a stored/submitted code exists, the link is created <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Player can manually enter a referral code via API (settings page) <!-- gap: no POST /referral/apply endpoint or profile UI -->\n- [x] Attempting to change an existing referrer returns an error <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 referee_wallet UNIQUE + db.ts:694 insertReferralLink throws on duplicate -->\n- [ ] Self-referral (referrer wallet = referee wallet) is rejected <!-- gap: no API-level validation implemented -->\n- [x] Referral link is stored in `referral_links` table with `created_at` timestamp <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:17-22 + db.ts:694-701 insertReferralLink -->\n\n### FR-3: Referee Fee Rebate\n\nReferred players receive a **fixed 10% rebate on their own fees** (1000 bps of fee_lamports), accruing as a claimable SOL balance. This is permanent and not configurable â€” every referred player gets 10% back on every game, forever.\n\n**Economics:**\n- On a 1 SOL wager with 500 bps fee: fee = 0.05 SOL, referee rebate = 0.005 SOL\n- Rebate is calculated and stored at settlement time, same transaction as the referrer earning\n- Fee is charged in full on-chain â€” rebate accrues off-chain as claimable SOL\n- Rebate shares the same claim flow as referrer earnings (unified pending balance per wallet)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] After a referred player's game settles, a rebate row is recorded in `referral_earnings.referee_rebate_lamports` <!-- gap: no settlement hook in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Rebate is exactly 1000 bps of fee_lamports (fixed, not configurable) <!-- gap: no calculation logic implemented -->\n- [ ] Rebate accrues to the referee's claimable balance (same claim flow as referrer earnings) <!-- gap: no claim flow or balance calculation -->\n- [ ] Benefit is communicated in the UI on the referral page and at code entry <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] A player who is both a referrer AND a referee sees a single combined pending balance <!-- gap: no balance aggregation logic -->\n\n### FR-4: Referrer Fee Share\n\nWhen a referred player completes a game, the referrer earns a share of the platform fee from that game. This is the core incentive loop.\n\n**Economics:**\n- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**","numLines":120,"startLine":1,"totalLines":715}}}
