{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CC7DjSTuywzKBVtSQTyeKn","type":"tool_result","content":"   120â†’- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n   121â†’- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n   122â†’- Source: platform fee â€” no new fees charged to players\n   123â†’- Duration: **permanent** â€” referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n   124â†’- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n   125â†’\n   126â†’**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n   127â†’\n   128â†’**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer â†’ calculates earnings â†’ inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n   129â†’\n   130â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131â†’- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n   132â†’- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n   133â†’- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n   134â†’- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n   135â†’- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n   136â†’\n   137â†’### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n   138â†’\n   139â†’Referrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n   140â†’\n   141â†’**Stats view:**\n   142â†’- Total referred players\n   143â†’- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n   144â†’- Total wager volume from referrals\n   145â†’- Total earnings (all time)\n   146â†’- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n   147â†’- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n   148â†’\n   149â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   150â†’- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   151â†’- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n   152â†’- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n   153â†’- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n   154â†’\n   155â†’### FR-6: Claim Flow\n   156â†’\n   157â†’Referrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n   158â†’\n   159â†’**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" â†’ backend validates balance > minimum threshold â†’ creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction â†’ returns 202 with claim ID â†’ frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` â†’ queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature â†’ claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) â†’ frontend shows final state.\n   160â†’\n   161â†’**Claim state machine:**\n   162â†’`pending -> processing -> completed`\n   163â†’`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n   164â†’\n   165â†’**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n   166â†’\n   167â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   168â†’- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n   169â†’- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n   170â†’- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n   171â†’- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n   172â†’- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n   173â†’- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n   174â†’- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n   175â†’- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5sâ†’30sâ†’300s) for all event types -->\n   176â†’\n   177â†’### FR-7: API Contract\n   178â†’\n   179â†’All referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n   180â†’\n   181â†’**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n   182â†’`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n   183â†’\n   184â†’```\n   185â†’POST /referral/code                â€” Set referral code\n   186â†’  Body: { code: string }\n   187â†’  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n   188â†’\n   189â†’GET  /referral/code                â€” Get current referral code\n   190â†’  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n   191â†’\n   192â†’POST /referral/apply               â€” Apply a referral code to current user\n   193â†’  Body: { code: string }\n   194â†’  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n   195â†’\n   196â†’GET  /referral/stats               â€” Get referral summary stats\n   197â†’  Response: {\n   198â†’    referredCount: number,\n   199â†’    activeCount: number,\n   200â†’    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n   201â†’    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n   202â†’    pendingLamports: string\n   203â†’  }\n   204â†’\n   205â†’GET  /referral/earnings            â€” Get detailed per-game earnings log\n   206â†’  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n   207â†’  Response: {\n   208â†’    items: [{\n   209â†’      roundId: string,\n   210â†’      gameType: string,\n   211â†’      refereeWallet: string,\n   212â†’      wagerLamports: string,\n   213â†’      earnedLamports: string,\n   214â†’      createdAt: string\n   215â†’    }],\n   216â†’    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n   217â†’  }\n   218â†’\n   219â†’POST /referral/claim               â€” Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n   220â†’  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n   221â†’\n   222â†’GET  /referral/claim/:claimId      â€” Poll claim status\n   223â†’  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n   224â†’```\n   225â†’\n   226â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   227â†’- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n   228â†’- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   229â†’- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   230â†’- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n   231â†’\n   232â†’### FR-8: Database Schema\n   233â†’\n   234â†’New tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n   235â†’\n   236â†’```sql\n   237â†’referral_codes (\n   238â†’  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   239â†’  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n   240â†’  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,   -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n   241â†’  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   242â†’  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   243â†’)\n   244â†’\n   245â†’referral_links (\n   246â†’  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   247â†’  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n   248â†’  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n   249â†’  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   250â†’)\n   251â†’\n   252â†’referral_earnings (\n   253â†’  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   254â†’  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n   255â†’  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   256â†’  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n   257â†’  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n   258â†’  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   259â†’  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   260â†’  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   261â†’  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n   262â†’  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   263â†’  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n   264â†’  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   265â†’  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n   266â†’)\n   267â†’\n   268â†’referral_claims (\n   269â†’  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n   270â†’  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n   271â†’  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n   272â†’  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n   273â†’  tx_signature      TEXT,\n   274â†’  error             TEXT,\n   275â†’  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   276â†’  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n   277â†’)\n   278â†’\n   279â†’-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\n   280â†’referral_kol_rates (\n   281â†’  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n   282â†’  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n   283â†’  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n   284â†’  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n   285â†’  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n   286â†’)\n   287â†’```\n   288â†’\n   289â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   290â†’- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n   291â†’- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 â€” referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   292â†’- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 â€” code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n   293â†’- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n   294â†’- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 â€” CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n   295â†’- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 â€” CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n   296â†’\n   297â†’### FR-9: Frontend â€” Routes, Pages, and Components\n   298â†’\n   299â†’All frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n   300â†’\n   301â†’#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` â€” Referral Link Handler\n   302â†’\n   303â†’A lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n   304â†’\n   305â†’**Flow:**\n   306â†’1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n   307â†’2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n   308â†’3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n   309â†’4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n   310â†’5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer â†’ calls `POST /referral/apply` â†’ clears localStorage on success\n   311â†’\n   312â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   313â†’- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   314â†’- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n   315â†’- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n   316â†’- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   317â†’- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n   318â†’- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n   319â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4718ef4b-5b78-4595-bd86-4abb58e68966","uuid":"0c43f7ce-89fa-4377-ba6f-b00208af0ddc","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:06:35.813Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n- Source: platform fee â€” no new fees charged to players\n- Duration: **permanent** â€” referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n\n**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n\n**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer â†’ calculates earnings â†’ inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n\n### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n\nReferrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n\n**Stats view:**\n- Total referred players\n- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n- Total wager volume from referrals\n- Total earnings (all time)\n- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n\n### FR-6: Claim Flow\n\nReferrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n\n**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" â†’ backend validates balance > minimum threshold â†’ creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction â†’ returns 202 with claim ID â†’ frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` â†’ queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature â†’ claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) â†’ frontend shows final state.\n\n**Claim state machine:**\n`pending -> processing -> completed`\n`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n\n**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5sâ†’30sâ†’300s) for all event types -->\n\n### FR-7: API Contract\n\nAll referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n\n**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n\n```\nPOST /referral/code                â€” Set referral code\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n\nGET  /referral/code                â€” Get current referral code\n  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n\nPOST /referral/apply               â€” Apply a referral code to current user\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n\nGET  /referral/stats               â€” Get referral summary stats\n  Response: {\n    referredCount: number,\n    activeCount: number,\n    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n    pendingLamports: string\n  }\n\nGET  /referral/earnings            â€” Get detailed per-game earnings log\n  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n  Response: {\n    items: [{\n      roundId: string,\n      gameType: string,\n      refereeWallet: string,\n      wagerLamports: string,\n      earnedLamports: string,\n      createdAt: string\n    }],\n    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n  }\n\nPOST /referral/claim               â€” Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n\nGET  /referral/claim/:claimId      â€” Poll claim status\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n\n### FR-8: Database Schema\n\nNew tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n\n```sql\nreferral_codes (\n  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n  code          TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,   -- player-chosen, 3-16 chars [a-z0-9-]\n  created_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at    TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_links (\n  id              SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet  TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,  -- one referrer per player\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n\nreferral_earnings (\n  id                        SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  referrer_wallet           TEXT NOT NULL,\n  referee_wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  round_id                  TEXT NOT NULL,\n  game_type                 TEXT NOT NULL,\n  wager_lamports            BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  fee_lamports              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_earned_lamports  BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referrer_rate_bps         INTEGER NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  referee_rebate_rate_bps   INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- always 1000 for v1\n  created_at                TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)  -- idempotency: one earning per player per round\n)\n\nreferral_claims (\n  id                UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),\n  wallet            TEXT NOT NULL,\n  amount_lamports   BIGINT NOT NULL,\n  status            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('pending','processing','completed','failed')),\n  tx_signature      TEXT,\n  error             TEXT,\n  requested_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  processed_at      TIMESTAMPTZ\n)\n\n-- KOL custom referrer rates (overrides default 1000 bps)\nreferral_kol_rates (\n  wallet          TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  rate_bps        INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- e.g., 2000 = 20% of total fee (= 100 bps of wager)\n  set_by          TEXT NOT NULL,     -- admin wallet\n  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now(),\n  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT now()\n)\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [x] All tables created via migration (referral_codes, referral_links, referral_earnings, referral_claims, referral_kol_rates) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates all 5 tables -->\n- [x] `referral_links.referee_wallet` has UNIQUE constraint (one referrer per player) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:22 â€” referee_wallet TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] `referral_codes.code` has UNIQUE constraint <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:12 â€” code TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE -->\n- [x] Appropriate indexes on wallet columns and `referral_earnings.round_id` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql â€” 6 indexes covering all wallet lookups and round_id -->\n- [x] `referral_earnings` has unique idempotency guard (`UNIQUE (referee_wallet, round_id)`) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:43-44 â€” CONSTRAINT uq_referral_earnings_referee_round -->\n- [x] `referral_claims.status` constrained to `pending|processing|completed|failed` <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql:67-68 â€” CHECK constraint chk_referral_claims_status -->\n\n### FR-9: Frontend â€” Routes, Pages, and Components\n\nAll frontend changes live in `apps/platform/`. Follows existing patterns: React Router routes in `App.tsx`, NavLink in `Sidebar.tsx`, feature code in `features/referral/`, API wrappers in `lib/referral-api.ts`.\n\n#### 9a. New Route: `/r/:code` â€” Referral Link Handler\n\nA lightweight route that captures the referral code from the URL, persists it, and redirects to the home page (or wherever the player was headed).\n\n**Flow:**\n1. Player visits `taunt.bet/r/my-code`\n2. Route component reads `:code` via `useParams()`\n3. Stores `{ code, capturedAt }` in `localStorage` key `referral_code`\n4. Redirects to `/` via `<Navigate to=\"/\" replace />`\n5. On next authentication (in `SessionContext` or a dedicated `useReferralApply` hook), if `referral_code` exists in localStorage and user has no referrer â†’ calls `POST /referral/apply` â†’ clears localStorage on success\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/r/:code` registered in `App.tsx` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Code stored in localStorage on visit (no auth required) <!-- gap: no localStorage referral code logic -->\n- [ ] Redirect to `/` happens immediately after capture <!-- gap: no route handler -->\n- [ ] On successful authentication, stored code is applied via API <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] localStorage is cleared after successful apply (or if code is invalid/already linked) <!-- gap: no apply logic -->\n- [ ] Invalid/expired codes show a toast notification, not a blocking error <!-- gap: no error handling -->\n","numLines":200,"startLine":120,"totalLines":715}}}
