{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014Lj5edE2aNXN6jamy3X6gJ","type":"tool_result","content":"   320â†’#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation â€” Referrals Link\n   321â†’\n   322â†’New nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n   323â†’\n   324â†’```tsx\n   325â†’<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n   326â†’  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n   327â†’  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n   328â†’    {/* share/link icon */}\n   329â†’  </div>\n   330â†’  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n   331â†’</NavLink>\n   332â†’```\n   333â†’\n   334â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   335â†’- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n   336â†’- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   337â†’- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   338â†’- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   339â†’\n   340â†’#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n   341â†’\n   342â†’Main referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n   343â†’\n   344â†’**Layout â€” top to bottom:**\n   345â†’\n   346â†’1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   347â†’   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button â†’ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` â†’ shows link\n   348â†’   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   349â†’   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   350â†’   - \"Change code\" link â†’ inline edit field to set a new custom code â†’ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n   351â†’\n   352â†’2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   353â†’   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   354â†’   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   355â†’   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports â†’ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   356â†’   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n   357â†’\n   358â†’3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   359â†’   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   360â†’   - \"Claim\" button â€” enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   361â†’   - Claim flow: button â†’ loading state â†’ calls `POST /referral/claim` â†’ success toast with tx link â†’ refresh stats\n   362â†’   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n   363â†’\n   364â†’4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   365â†’   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   366â†’   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   367â†’   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   368â†’   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n   369â†’\n   370â†’**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n   371â†’\n   372â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   373â†’- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n   374â†’- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n   375â†’- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n   376â†’- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n   377â†’- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n   378â†’- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n   379â†’- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n   380â†’- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n   381â†’- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n   382â†’- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n   383â†’\n   384â†’#### 9d. Profile Settings â€” Referral Code Input\n   385â†’\n   386â†’In the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n   387â†’\n   388â†’**Layout:**\n   389â†’- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n   390â†’- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n   391â†’- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n   392â†’- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n   393â†’\n   394â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   395â†’- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n   396â†’- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   397â†’- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   398â†’- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   399â†’- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   400â†’\n   401â†’#### 9e. API Client â€” `lib/referral-api.ts`\n   402â†’\n   403â†’Thin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n   404â†’\n   405â†’```typescript\n   406â†’const BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n   407â†’\n   408â†’export async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   409â†’export async function getReferralCode(token: string);\n   410â†’export async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\n   411â†’export async function getReferralStats(token: string);\n   412â†’export async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\n   413â†’export async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\n   414â†’export async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n   415â†’```\n   416â†’\n   417â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   418â†’- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n   419â†’- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   420â†’- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   421â†’- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n   422â†’\n   423â†’#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook â€” `useReferralApply`\n   424â†’\n   425â†’A hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n   426â†’\n   427â†’```typescript\n   428â†’// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\n   429â†’export function useReferralApply() {\n   430â†’  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n   431â†’  const { address } = useWallet();\n   432â†’\n   433â†’  useEffect(() => {\n   434â†’    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n   435â†’    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n   436â†’    if (!stored) return;\n   437â†’    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n   438â†’    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n   439â†’      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n   440â†’      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n   441â†’  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n   442â†’}\n   443â†’```\n   444â†’\n   445â†’Mount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n   446â†’\n   447â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   448â†’- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n   449â†’- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   450â†’- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   451â†’- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) â€” retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   452â†’- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   453â†’- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n   454â†’\n   455â†’### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n   456â†’\n   457â†’The referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n   458â†’\n   459â†’**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n   460â†’1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n   461â†’2. If referrer exists â†’ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports Ă— referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports Ă— fee_bps / 10000)\n   462â†’3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n   463â†’4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n   464â†’\n   465â†’**Referrer rate lookup:**\n   466â†’1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n   467â†’2. If found â†’ use KOL rate\n   468â†’3. If not â†’ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   469â†’\n   470â†’**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n   471â†’\n   472â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   473â†’- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n   474â†’- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n   475â†’- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n   476â†’- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n   477â†’- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n   478â†’- [ ] No additional RPC calls â€” purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n   479â†’- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n   480â†’\n   481â†’---\n   482â†’\n   483â†’### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n   484â†’\n   485â†’Referral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n   486â†’\n   487â†’**Event types (v1):**\n   488â†’- `referral.claim_requested` â€” emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n   489â†’\n   490â†’Note: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings â€” only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n   491â†’\n   492â†’**Payload contract:**\n   493â†’\n   494â†’`referral.claim_requested`\n   495â†’```json\n   496â†’{\n   497â†’  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n   498â†’  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n   499â†’  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n   500â†’  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n   501â†’}\n   502â†’```\n   503â†’\n   504â†’**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n   505â†’\n   506â†’**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   507â†’- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n   508â†’- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n   509â†’- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   510â†’- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   511â†’- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   512â†’- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n   513â†’\n   514â†’---\n   515â†’\n   516â†’## Design Decisions (v1)\n   517â†’\n   518â†’### Why immutable referrer linkage\n   519â†’\n   520â†’- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n   521â†’- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n   522â†’- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n   523â†’\n   524â†’### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n   525â†’\n   526â†’- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n   527â†’- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n   528â†’- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n   529â†’\n   530â†’### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n   531â†’\n   532â†’- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n   533â†’- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n   534â†’- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n   535â†’\n   536â†’---\n   537â†’\n   538â†’## Success Criteria\n   539â†’\n   540â†’- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n   541â†’- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n   542â†’- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n   543â†’- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n   544â†’- No on-chain program changes required â€” entirely off-chain for v1\n   545â†’- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n   546â†’- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n   547â†’\n   548â†’---\n   549â†’\n   550â†’## Dependencies\n   551â†’\n   552â†’- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n   553â†’- **Async event queue (spec 301)** â€” referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n   554â†’- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n   555â†’- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n   556â†’- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n   557â†’- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n   558â†’\n   559â†’## Assumptions\n   560â†’\n   561â†’- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n   562â†’- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n   563â†’- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n   564â†’- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n   565â†’- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ â€” already met)\n   566â†’\n   567â†’---\n   568â†’\n   569â†’## Validation Plan\n   570â†’\n   571â†’| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   572â†’|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   573â†’| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n   574â†’| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n   575â†’| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n   576â†’| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n   577â†’| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n   578â†’| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n   579â†’| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n   580â†’| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n   581â†’| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n   582â†’| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n   583â†’| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n   584â†’| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n   585â†’| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim â†’ poll status â†’ verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n   586â†’| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code â†’ verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n   587â†’| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n   588â†’| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n   589â†’| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n   590â†’| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n   591â†’| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n   592â†’| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n   593â†’| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n   594â†’| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n   595â†’| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n   596â†’\n   597â†’---\n   598â†’\n   599â†’## Completion Signal\n   600â†’\n   601â†’### Implementation Checklist\n   602â†’\n   603â†’#### Prerequisite\n   604â†’- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n   605â†’\n   606â†’#### Backend â€” Database & Core\n   607â†’- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n   608â†’- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n   609â†’- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n   610â†’- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n   611â†’- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n   612â†’\n   613â†’#### Backend â€” API Endpoints\n   614â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` â€” set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n   615â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` â€” return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n   616â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` â€” link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n   617â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` â€” return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n   618â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` â€” paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n   619â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` â€” validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7) (done: iteration 12)\n   620â†’- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` â€” return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7) (done: iteration 13)\n   621â†’- [x] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware (done: iteration 14)\n   622â†’\n   623â†’#### Backend â€” Settlement Integration\n   624â†’- [x] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10) (done: iteration 15)\n   625â†’- [x] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity â€” referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4) (done: iteration 16)\n   626â†’\n   627â†’#### Backend â€” Claim Queue Handler\n   628â†’- [x] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11) (done: iteration 17)\n   629â†’\n   630â†’#### Frontend â€” API Client & Plumbing\n   631â†’- [x] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` â€” 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e) (done: iteration 18)\n   632â†’- [x] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` â€” capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a) (done: iteration 19)\n   633â†’- [x] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook â€” on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f) (done: iteration 20)\n   634â†’\n   635â†’#### Frontend â€” Referral Page\n   636â†’- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n   637â†’- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n   638â†’- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§1: \"Your Referral Link\" card â€” custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c Â§1)\n   639â†’- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§2: Stats summary card â€” four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamportsâ†’SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c Â§2)\n   640â†’- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§3: Pending balance card â€” show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c Â§3, FR-6)\n   641â†’- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§4: Earnings history table â€” paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c Â§4)\n   642â†’- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n   643â†’\n   644â†’#### Testing\n   645â†’- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n   646â†’- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player â†’ verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n   647â†’- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n   648â†’- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n   649â†’- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) â†’ commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) â†’ save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** â†’ fix code\n   650â†’- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n   651â†’\n   652â†’### Testing Requirements\n   653â†’\n   654â†’The agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n   655â†’\n   656â†’#### Code Quality\n   657â†’- [ ] All existing tests pass\n   658â†’- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n   659â†’- [ ] No lint errors\n   660â†’\n   661â†’#### Functional Verification\n   662â†’- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n   663â†’- [ ] Edge cases handled\n   664â†’- [ ] Error states handled\n   665â†’\n   666â†’#### Visual Regression\n   667â†’- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n   668â†’- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n   669â†’- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n   670â†’- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n   671â†’\n   672â†’#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n   673â†’- [ ] Desktop view correct\n   674â†’- [ ] Mobile view correct\n   675â†’\n   676â†’#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n   677â†’- [ ] No JS console errors\n   678â†’- [ ] No failed network requests\n   679â†’\n   680â†’#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n   681â†’\n   682â†’Before declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\n   683â†’makes sense from a player's perspective.\n   684â†’\n   685â†’- [ ] Set custom referral code â†’ copy link â†’ verify URL format\n   686â†’- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito â†’ authenticate â†’ verify referrer linked\n   687â†’- [ ] Manually enter code in settings â†’ verify referrer linked\n   688â†’- [ ] Play a game as referred player â†’ verify referrer earnings appear\n   689â†’- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n   690â†’- [ ] Claim earnings â†’ verify SOL arrives in wallet\n   691â†’- [ ] Attempt self-referral â†’ verify blocked\n   692â†’- [ ] Attempt to change referrer â†’ verify blocked\n   693â†’- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n   694â†’- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n   695â†’\n   696â†’### Iteration Instructions\n   697â†’\n   698â†’If ANY check fails:\n   699â†’1. Identify the specific issue\n   700â†’2. Fix the code\n   701â†’3. Re-run tests\n   702â†’4. Re-verify all criteria\n   703â†’5. Check again\n   704â†’\n   705â†’**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   706â†’\n   707â†’### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n   708â†’\n   709â†’After the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n   710â†’`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n   711â†’1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n   712â†’2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n   713â†’3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n   714â†’4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n   715â†’"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4718ef4b-5b78-4595-bd86-4abb58e68966","uuid":"f14d135d-eac6-4b8f-85b4-39761da86658","timestamp":"2026-03-25T13:06:40.625Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"#### 9b. Sidebar Navigation â€” Referrals Link\n\nNew nav item in the \"Player\" section of `Sidebar.tsx`, between \"Quests\" and the \"Platform\" section.\n\n```tsx\n<NavLink to=\"/referrals\" className={({ isActive }) => `nv-item ${isActive ? \"active\" : \"\"}`}\n  style={{ \"--nc\": \"var(--color-green)\" } as React.CSSProperties}>\n  <div className=\"nv-ico\">\n    {/* share/link icon */}\n  </div>\n  <span className=\"nv-lbl\">Referrals</span>\n</NavLink>\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] \"Referrals\" nav item appears in sidebar under \"Player\" section <!-- gap: not in Sidebar.tsx -->\n- [ ] Active state styling matches existing nav items <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Icon is a share/link-style SVG consistent with sidebar icon style <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Navigates to `/referrals` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9c. Referral Page (`/referrals`)\n\nMain referral hub page at route `/referrals`. Requires wallet connection + authentication. Shows different states based on whether the player has generated a code yet.\n\n**Layout â€” top to bottom:**\n\n1. **Your Referral Link** (card)\n   - If no code yet: input field to choose a custom code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button â†’ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }` â†’ shows link\n   - If code exists: display code + full URL in a styled input/box with a **Copy Link** button\n   - Copy uses `navigator.clipboard.writeText(url)` with a brief \"Copied!\" feedback (tooltip or button text swap)\n   - \"Change code\" link â†’ inline edit field to set a new custom code â†’ calls `POST /referral/code { code: \"...\" }`\n\n2. **Stats Summary** (card or stat row)\n   - Four stat boxes in a row: Referred Players | Active (7d) | Total Volume | Total Earned\n   - Values from `GET /referral/stats`\n   - SOL values formatted with `BalanceDisplay` or equivalent (lamports â†’ SOL, 4 decimal places)\n   - Skeleton/loading state while fetching\n\n3. **Pending Earnings + Claim** (card)\n   - Shows pending (unclaimed) balance prominently\n   - \"Claim\" button â€” enabled only when pending > minimum threshold (0.01 SOL)\n   - Claim flow: button â†’ loading state â†’ calls `POST /referral/claim` â†’ success toast with tx link â†’ refresh stats\n   - Error state: if claim fails, show error message + retry option\n\n4. **Earnings History** (table)\n   - Paginated table from `GET /referral/earnings`\n   - Columns: Date | Game | Referee (truncated wallet) | Wager | Your Earning\n   - Empty state: \"No earnings yet. Share your link to start earning!\"\n   - Pagination controls at bottom (page numbers or \"Load more\")\n\n**Not-connected state:** Show a prompt to connect wallet + brief explanation of the referral program.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Route `/referrals` registered in `App.tsx`, renders `ReferralPage` <!-- gap: not in App.tsx routes -->\n- [ ] Unauthenticated users see a connect-wallet prompt with referral program description <!-- gap: no ReferralPage component -->\n- [ ] Code input validates (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) and shows errors inline <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Setting a code displays the referral URL <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Copy button copies full URL to clipboard with visual feedback <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Stats summary loads from API and displays correctly with loading skeleton <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Claim button is disabled when below threshold, shows loading during claim <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Successful claim shows toast with transaction link (Solana explorer) <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Earnings table loads paginated data with correct columns <!-- gap: no component -->\n- [ ] Empty states have meaningful messages for each section <!-- gap: no component -->\n\n#### 9d. Profile Settings â€” Referral Code Input\n\nIn the existing profile page (`/profile`, settings tab), add a \"Referral Code\" section where players can manually enter a referral code if they didn't arrive via a referral link.\n\n**Layout:**\n- Section header: \"Referral Code\"\n- If no referrer linked: text input + \"Apply\" button\n- If referrer already linked: display \"Referred by: [truncated wallet]\" (read-only)\n- Error states: \"Invalid code\", \"Already linked to a referrer\", \"Cannot refer yourself\"\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral code input section added to profile settings tab <!-- gap: not in profile components -->\n- [ ] Input calls `POST /referral/apply` on submit <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] If already referred, shows referrer wallet (read-only, non-editable) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Validation errors display inline (not just console) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Self-referral attempt shows clear error message <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9e. API Client â€” `lib/referral-api.ts`\n\nThin fetch wrappers following the pattern in `lib/auth-api.ts`. All calls require JWT from `useSession().accessToken`.\n\n```typescript\nconst BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\";\n\nexport async function setReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralCode(token: string);\nexport async function applyReferralCode(token: string, code: string);\nexport async function getReferralStats(token: string);\nexport async function getReferralEarnings(token: string, page?: number, limit?: number);\nexport async function requestReferralClaim(token: string);\nexport async function pollClaimStatus(token: string, claimId: string);\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All 7 API functions implemented (`setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus`) with JWT Bearer auth header <!-- gap: lib/referral-api.ts does not exist -->\n- [ ] Response parsing follows `parseResponse<T>()` pattern from `auth-api.ts` <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Error responses surface user-friendly messages (not raw HTTP status) <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n- [ ] Functions are typed with request/response interfaces <!-- gap: not implemented -->\n\n#### 9f. Referral Apply Hook â€” `useReferralApply`\n\nA hook that runs on authentication to auto-apply stored referral codes from localStorage.\n\n```typescript\n// In features/referral/hooks/useReferralApply.ts\nexport function useReferralApply() {\n  const { isAuthenticated, accessToken } = useSession();\n  const { address } = useWallet();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken || !address) return;\n    const stored = localStorage.getItem(\"referral_code\");\n    if (!stored) return;\n    const { code } = JSON.parse(stored);\n    applyReferralCode(accessToken, code)\n      .then(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* toast: linked! */ })\n      .catch(() => { localStorage.removeItem(\"referral_code\"); /* silent or toast */ });\n  }, [isAuthenticated, accessToken, address]);\n}\n```\n\nMount in `App.tsx` (inside auth provider tree) so it runs globally on every login.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Hook reads referral code from localStorage after successful authentication <!-- gap: no useReferralApply hook -->\n- [ ] Calls `POST /referral/apply` automatically <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Clears localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid code, already linked) <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Does not clear localStorage on transient failure (network error) â€” retries next auth <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Shows a subtle success toast when a referral link is auto-applied <!-- gap: no hook -->\n- [ ] Mounted in `App.tsx` or `AppContent` so it activates on any page <!-- gap: no hook -->\n\n### FR-10: Backend Settlement Integration\n\nThe referral earnings calculation hooks into the existing settlement worker. No new services or workers needed.\n\n**Hook point:** After a game round/match settles successfully (settlement writes the outcome to DB), the settlement logic:\n1. Looks up the player's referrer in `referral_links`\n2. If referrer exists â†’ calculates `referrer_earned_lamports = fee_lamports Ă— referrer_rate_bps / 10000` (where fee_lamports = wager_lamports Ă— fee_bps / 10000)\n3. Inserts row into `referral_earnings`\n4. Inserts `referral.game_settled` event into `event_queue` (same DB transaction) for downstream reward processing\n\n**Referrer rate lookup:**\n1. Check `referral_kol_rates` for the referrer's wallet\n2. If found â†’ use KOL rate\n3. If not â†’ use default rate from config/env (default: 1000 bps = 10% of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n\n**Performance:** Single DB query (join `referral_links` + optional `referral_kol_rates`) per settled game. Cached in-memory for hot wallets if needed later.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Settlement worker checks for referrer after each game settlement <!-- gap: no referral logic in settle-tx.ts -->\n- [ ] Referrer earnings are calculated using correct formula (bps of total fee, not total wager) <!-- gap: no calculation logic -->\n- [ ] KOL custom rate is used when present, default rate otherwise <!-- gap: no rate lookup in settlement -->\n- [ ] Earnings row is inserted in the same DB transaction as settlement (atomicity) <!-- gap: no transactional referral write -->\n- [ ] Referral event emitted to async queue for downstream processing (referee rewards, notifications) <!-- gap: no event emission in settlement -->\n- [ ] No additional RPC calls â€” purely DB-level <!-- gap: not yet applicable -->\n- [ ] Settlement latency increase is negligible (< 5ms additional) <!-- gap: not yet measurable -->\n\n---\n\n### FR-11: Referral Event Contracts + Handler Idempotency\n\nReferral feature handlers are queue consumers built on spec 301 infrastructure.\n\n**Event types (v1):**\n- `referral.claim_requested` â€” emitted after claim request row is created. Handler sends SOL from treasury.\n\nNote: `referral.game_settled` earnings are written synchronously in the settlement transaction (same DB tx). No async handler needed for earnings â€” only for claims, where the SOL transfer is the slow/unreliable part.\n\n**Payload contract:**\n\n`referral.claim_requested`\n```json\n{\n  \"claimId\": \"uuid\",\n  \"wallet\": \"string\",\n  \"amountLamports\": \"string\",\n  \"requestedAt\": \"ISO-8601 timestamp\"\n}\n```\n\n**Idempotency key:** `referral:claim:{claimId}`\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] `referral.claim_requested` event emitted with the payload above when a claim is created <!-- gap: no claim endpoint to emit events -->\n- [ ] Handler validates payload shape; malformed payloads are dead-lettered <!-- gap: no handler registered -->\n- [ ] Handler performs idempotency check: if claim already completed/failed, no-op <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler re-verifies available balance before transfer (prevents overpay on concurrent claims) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Handler sends SOL from treasury to wallet, records tx_signature in `referral_claims` <!-- gap: no handler -->\n- [ ] Re-processing the same event is a safe no-op (no duplicate SOL transfers) <!-- gap: no handler -->\n\n---\n\n## Design Decisions (v1)\n\n### Why immutable referrer linkage\n\n- Prevents referral hijacking and user confusion.\n- Simplifies all downstream aggregation and payout logic.\n- Keeps fraud analysis tractable (single parent per user graph).\n\n### Why async claims (not synchronous transfer API)\n\n- Wallet RPC operations are the slowest and least reliable part of the flow.\n- Async queue gives retries/backoff and keeps user request latency low.\n- Prevents backend API threads from being tied up by treasury transfer delays.\n\n### Why persist economic inputs in `referral_earnings`\n\n- Store `fee_lamports` + `referrer_rate_bps` with each earning row to preserve historical correctness.\n- Future rate changes do not retroactively affect past earnings or audits.\n- Makes dispute/debug workflows deterministic from DB data alone.\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Players can set a custom code, share it, and apply referral codes without friction\n- Referral earnings are calculated correctly and match expected economics (1000 bps of total fee = 50 bps of wager)\n- Claim flow delivers SOL to the player's wallet reliably\n- System handles concurrent operations without double-crediting or double-claiming\n- No on-chain program changes required â€” entirely off-chain for v1\n- Settlement path latency is not measurably affected by referral logic\n- Rewards and claims are processed async via event queue (spec 301) without blocking game loops\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Existing JWT authentication system (spec 007)\n- **Async event queue (spec 301)** â€” referee rewards and claim payouts are processed via the queue\n- Backend settlement worker (must be extended with referral earnings hook + event emission)\n- Treasury wallet with sufficient SOL for claim payouts\n- Frontend routing for `/r/{CODE}` deep links\n- Environment variables for default referral rate (`REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS=1000`) and claim threshold (`REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS=10000000`)\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Fee structure is 500 bps (5%) flat fee to single treasury (PlatformConfig on-chain)\n- Treasury wallet is funded and managed outside this spec\n- Referral system launches alongside or after existing games (coinflip, lord-of-rngs)\n- No on-chain enforcement of referral economics needed for v1\n- Postgres `SKIP LOCKED` is available (Postgres 9.5+ â€” already met)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Code generation works | API test: generate code, verify format and DB entry | Test output |\n| 2 | Custom codes validated | API test: valid/invalid custom codes | Test output |\n| 3 | Referral linking via URL | E2E: visit /r/CODE, authenticate, verify link created | Test output + DB check |\n| 4 | Manual code entry works | API test: apply code via endpoint | Test output |\n| 5 | Self-referral blocked | API test: apply own code, expect 400 | Test output |\n| 6 | Immutable referrer | API test: apply second code after first, expect 409 | Test output |\n| 7 | Earnings calculated at settlement | Integration test: settle game for referred player, check referral_earnings | Test output + DB check |\n| 8 | KOL custom rate applied | Integration test: set KOL rate, settle game, verify different earning | Test output |\n| 9 | Stats endpoint accurate | API test: create referrals + earnings, verify stats math | Test output |\n| 10 | Claim delivers SOL | Integration test: claim flow, verify tx on-chain | Tx signature |\n| 11 | Concurrent claim prevention | Load test: parallel claims, verify only one succeeds | Test output |\n| 12 | Referee bonus reward granted | Integration test: apply code + complete game, verify reward trigger fired via queue | Test output + DB check |\n| 21 | Async claim completes via queue | Integration test: POST claim â†’ poll status â†’ verify completed with tx sig | Test output + Tx sig |\n| 22 | Welcome reward fires on code apply | Integration test: apply code â†’ verify `referral.code_applied` event processed | Test output + DB check |\n| 23 | Queue infrastructure works (spec 301) | See spec 301 validation plan | Per spec 301 |\n| 13 | `/r/:code` captures + redirects | E2E: visit referral URL, check localStorage, verify redirect to `/` | Browser test |\n| 14 | Auto-apply on auth | E2E: store code in localStorage, connect wallet, verify referral link created + localStorage cleared | Browser test |\n| 15 | Referral page renders all sections | Visual test: code card, stats, claim, earnings table in correct layout | Screenshot |\n| 16 | Copy link works | E2E: click copy button, verify clipboard content matches referral URL | Browser test |\n| 17 | Sidebar nav item present | Visual test: \"Referrals\" link visible in Player section, active state works | Screenshot |\n| 18 | Profile settings code input | E2E: enter code in profile settings, verify referral linked | Browser test |\n| 19 | Unauthenticated state | Visual test: `/referrals` without wallet shows connect prompt | Screenshot |\n| 20 | Claim button states | E2E: disabled when below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with tx link | Browser test |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n#### Prerequisite\n- [x] [backend] Event queue infrastructure implemented per spec 301 (completed in spec 301)\n\n#### Backend â€” Database & Core\n- [x] [backend] Database migration `011_referral.sql`: create `referral_codes`, `referral_links`, `referral_earnings`, `referral_claims`, `referral_kol_rates` tables with all constraints and indexes per FR-8 (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods in `db.ts`: `insertReferralCode`, `getReferralCodeByWallet`, `getReferralCodeByCode`, `upsertReferralCode` for code CRUD (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralLink`, `getReferralLinkByReferee`, referral link queries (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralEarning`, `getPendingBalance(wallet)` (sum referrer_earned where wallet=referrer + sum referee_rebate where wallet=referee, minus completed claims), `getReferralEarnings(wallet, page, limit)`, `getReferralStats(wallet)` (done: iteration 5)\n- [x] [backend] DB client methods: `insertReferralClaim`, `getReferralClaim`, `updateClaimStatus`, `getReferrerRate(wallet)` (check kol_rates, fallback to env default) (done: iteration 6)\n\n#### Backend â€” API Endpoints\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/code` â€” set player-chosen code (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`, unique). Requires JWT auth. Returns `{ code, url }` (FR-1, FR-7) (done: iteration 7)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/code` â€” return current code for authenticated wallet, or 404 (FR-7) (done: iteration 8)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/apply` â€” link referee to referrer. Validate: code exists, no self-referral, no existing referrer. Returns `{ referrer, benefit: \"10% fee rebate on all games\" }` (FR-2, FR-7) (done: iteration 9)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/stats` â€” return referredCount, activeCount (7d), totalVolumeLamports, totalEarnedLamports, pendingLamports for authenticated wallet. All values as lamport strings (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 10)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/earnings` â€” paginated per-game earnings log with roundId, gameType, refereeWallet, wagerLamports, earnedLamports, createdAt. Query params: page, limit (FR-5, FR-7) (done: iteration 11)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `POST /referral/claim` â€” validate pending balance > min threshold (env `REFERRAL_MIN_CLAIM_LAMPORTS`, default 10M = 0.01 SOL), snapshot amount, insert claim row + emit `referral.claim_requested` event in same DB tx. Return 202 `{ claimId, amountLamports, status: \"pending\" }` (FR-6, FR-7) (done: iteration 12)\n- [x] [backend] `routes/referral.ts`: `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` â€” return claim status + txSignature if completed (FR-7) (done: iteration 13)\n- [x] [backend] Register referral routes in `index.ts`, mount at `/referral` prefix with JWT auth middleware (done: iteration 14)\n\n#### Backend â€” Settlement Integration\n- [x] [backend] Settlement hook in `settle-tx.ts`: after each game settlement DB write, check `referral_links` for the settled player(s). If referrer exists, calculate `referrer_earned = fee_lamports * referrer_rate_bps / 10000` and `referee_rebate = fee_lamports * 1000 / 10000` (fixed 10%). Insert into `referral_earnings` in the same DB transaction. Use `getReferrerRate(wallet)` for KOL override (FR-4, FR-10) (done: iteration 15)\n- [x] [backend] Wrap settlement DB writes in `sql.transaction()` for atomicity â€” referral earning insert MUST be in the same transaction as the game settlement update (FR-10 + System Invariant 4) (done: iteration 16)\n\n#### Backend â€” Claim Queue Handler\n- [x] [backend] Register `referral.claim_requested` handler in queue registry: load claim by ID, verify status is `pending`, update to `processing`, re-verify available balance >= claim amount, execute SOL transfer from server keypair (treasury) to wallet, record tx_signature, update status to `completed`. On failure: record error, update status to `failed`. Idempotent: skip if status is already `completed` (FR-6, FR-11) (done: iteration 17)\n\n#### Frontend â€” API Client & Plumbing\n- [x] [frontend] `lib/referral-api.ts` â€” 7 typed fetch wrappers with JWT Bearer auth following `auth-api.ts` pattern: `setReferralCode`, `getReferralCode`, `applyReferralCode`, `getReferralStats`, `getReferralEarnings`, `requestReferralClaim`, `pollClaimStatus` (FR-9e) (done: iteration 18)\n- [x] [frontend] `/r/:code` route in `App.tsx` â€” capture code to `localStorage` key `referral_code` as `{ code, capturedAt }`, redirect to `/` via `<Navigate replace />` (FR-9a) (done: iteration 19)\n- [x] [frontend] `useReferralApply` hook â€” on authentication, if `referral_code` in localStorage and user has no referrer, call `POST /referral/apply`. Clear localStorage on success or permanent failure (invalid/already linked). Keep on transient failure. Show success toast. Mount in `App.tsx` inside auth provider tree (FR-9f) (done: iteration 20)\n\n#### Frontend â€” Referral Page\n- [ ] [frontend] Sidebar nav item \"Referrals\" in Player section of `Sidebar.tsx` with share/link icon, `--nc: var(--color-green)`, navigates to `/referrals` (FR-9b)\n- [ ] [frontend] `/referrals` route + `ReferralPage` shell: unauthenticated state shows connect-wallet prompt with referral program description. Authenticated state renders feature sections. Wrap in `RouteErrorBoundary` (FR-9c)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§1: \"Your Referral Link\" card â€” custom code input (3-16 chars, `[a-z0-9-]`) + \"Set Code\" button (if none), display code + full URL + Copy Link button with clipboard feedback. \"Change code\" option with inline validation (FR-9c Â§1)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§2: Stats summary card â€” four stat boxes (Referred Players, Active 7d, Total Volume, Total Earned) from `GET /referral/stats`. SOL values via lamportsâ†’SOL formatting. Loading skeleton (FR-9c Â§2)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§3: Pending balance card â€” show unified pending balance prominently. Breakdown: \"From referrals: X SOL\" + \"From fee rebates: Y SOL\". Claim button disabled below threshold, loading during claim, success toast with Solana explorer tx link (FR-9c Â§3, FR-6)\n- [ ] [frontend] Referral page Â§4: Earnings history table â€” paginated from `GET /referral/earnings`. Columns: Date, Game, Referee (truncated wallet), Wager, Your Earning. Empty state message. Pagination controls (FR-9c Â§4)\n- [ ] [frontend] Profile settings: \"Referral Code\" section in profile settings tab. If no referrer: input + Apply button. If already referred: read-only \"Referred by: [wallet]\". Error states inline (FR-9d)\n\n#### Testing\n- [ ] [test] Backend unit tests for referral routes: set custom code (happy path + validation + uniqueness), apply (happy path + self-referral + duplicate), stats, earnings pagination, claim flow (happy + zero balance + below threshold + concurrent)\n- [ ] [test] Backend integration test: settle a game for a referred player â†’ verify `referral_earnings` row with correct referrer_earned + referee_rebate amounts\n- [ ] [test] Add local deterministic E2E coverage for primary user flow(s) in `e2e/local/**` (or mark N/A with reason for non-web/non-interactive specs)\n- [ ] [test] Add visual route/state coverage in `e2e/visual/**`; run `pnpm test:visual` and update baselines only for intentional UI changes\n- [ ] [test] Update visual baselines for `/referrals` page (new page) and sidebar (new nav item). Run `pnpm test:visual` to identify failures, then `pnpm test:visual:update` to regenerate. **Before committing**: read old baseline and new screenshot for each changed page (use Read tool on PNG files). Evaluate: **PASS** (changes clearly match spec intent) â†’ commit; **REVIEW** (unexpected areas changed) â†’ save diff images to `docs/specs/300-referral-system/visual-review/`, describe concerns; **FAIL** â†’ fix code\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is included, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n\n### Testing Requirements\n\nThe agent MUST complete ALL before outputting the completion signal:\n\n#### Code Quality\n- [ ] All existing tests pass\n- [ ] New tests added for new functionality\n- [ ] No lint errors\n\n#### Functional Verification\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified\n- [ ] Edge cases handled\n- [ ] Error states handled\n\n#### Visual Regression\n- [ ] `pnpm test:visual` passes (all baselines match)\n- [ ] If this spec changes UI: affected baselines regenerated and committed\n- [ ] Local deterministic E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e`) for user-facing flows, or N/A documented\n- [ ] Devnet real-provider E2E passes (`pnpm test:e2e:devnet`) when provider-backed flows are included\n\n#### Visual Verification (if UI)\n- [ ] Desktop view correct\n- [ ] Mobile view correct\n\n#### Console/Network Check (if web)\n- [ ] No JS console errors\n- [ ] No failed network requests\n\n#### Smoke Test (Human-in-the-Loop)\n\nBefore declaring done, trace every user-facing flow and verify the experience\nmakes sense from a player's perspective.\n\n- [ ] Set custom referral code â†’ copy link â†’ verify URL format\n- [ ] Visit referral link in incognito â†’ authenticate â†’ verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Manually enter code in settings â†’ verify referrer linked\n- [ ] Play a game as referred player â†’ verify referrer earnings appear\n- [ ] Referrer dashboard shows correct stats\n- [ ] Claim earnings â†’ verify SOL arrives in wallet\n- [ ] Attempt self-referral â†’ verify blocked\n- [ ] Attempt to change referrer â†’ verify blocked\n- [ ] Referee fee rebate accrues after playing a game (visible in pending balance)\n- [ ] Referral page shows breakdown: \"From referrals: X\" + \"From fee rebates: Y\"\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nIf ANY check fails:\n1. Identify the specific issue\n2. Fix the code\n3. Re-run tests\n4. Re-verify all criteria\n5. Check again\n\n**Only when ALL checks pass, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n\n### Post-Completion: Gap Analysis\n\nAfter the spec loop outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`, `spec-loop.sh` automatically runs\n`/gap-analysis {id} --non-interactive` which:\n1. Audits every FR acceptance criterion against the codebase\n2. Writes `docs/specs/{id}/gap-analysis.md` with inventory + audit + recommendations\n3. Annotates FR checkboxes with HTML comment evidence (`<!-- satisfied: ... -->`)\n4. Commits everything together with the completion commit\n","numLines":396,"startLine":320,"totalLines":715}}}
